  "text": "More recently, [CITATION_1] find that exchange rate depreciation does not seem to be significant driver of exports growth in India, in the postreform period. In fact, imports seem to have a significant positive impact on exports, suggesting that imports support exports through improving domestic innovation and productivity and improving the export competitiveness.",
